error: bsql: query not found in offline cache (hash fffb761d7447997e)
         SQL: select nonexistent_column_xyz from users where id = $1

         Cache has 161 .bitcode files but this query's hash is not among them — the SQL has likely changed since the cache was built.

         To fix:
         1) Set DATABASE_URL (or BSQL_DATABASE_URL) to a live PostgreSQL
            and run `cargo build`. This regenerates the cache.
         2) Commit the entire `.bsql/queries/` directory to git:
            `git add .bsql/queries/ && git commit`
            Make sure ALL `.bitcode` files are staged, not just `.manifest`.
         3) On CI / prod, set `BSQL_OFFLINE=true` and build — no DB needed.
         4) Run `bsql verify` locally to confirm the cache is self-consistent
            before pushing.
